# `target/` (unanchored) also catches nested crates/*/target from a cargo run
# with cwd inside a crate — the anchored `/target` let those leak into status.
target/
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak
.DS_Store
.env
*.log
/dist/
/oxide.toml
# Runtime config oxide writes into whatever dir it's launched from (e.g. a crate
# dir during a test run) — never tracked.
**/oxide.toml
.oxide/sessions/
.oxide/memory/
.oxide/**/.DS_Store
**/.oxide/sessions/
**/.oxide/memory/
**/.oxide/checkpoints/
.oxide/trash/
**/.oxide/trash/
oxide-macos-arm64
# Release artifacts are built + attached by CI (release.yml) — never tracked.
# A 12MB gz committed 78× is what ballooned .git to 1GB.
oxide-macos-arm64.gz
oxide-macos-arm64.gz.sha256
.tmp/
**/.oxide/worktrees/
**/.oxide/screenshots/
**/.oxide/board.json
.oxide/worktrees/
.oxide/index/
**/.oxide/index/
.oxide/attachments/
**/.oxide/attachments/
